      class  OrderedTriple
      For all sets a and b, define OrderedTriple(a,b,c) as new OrderedPairAlternate(new OrderedPairAlternate(a), new OrderedPairAlternate(b,c)).
      class  Pair
      The Axiom of Pair: Given two sets x and y, there exists a set {x,y} that contains exactly them both.
      class  Powerset

      class  Singleton
      Singleton Theorem: For every set x, there exists a set that contains exactly x.
      class  Subset
      The Axiom of Specification: For every set x, and a proposition p, there exists a set y such that: for all sets t, if t is an element of y then t is an element of x and p(t) is true.
      class  Tuple
      A Tuple (an ordered n-tuple) is the generalized concept of an ordered pair.
